<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Add Payment</title>
<style type="text/css">
.underline{
	text-decoration: underline;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div>
	<b>Fields on <span class="underline">Payment Screen</span> :</b><br/><br/>
	<b>DO NOT SAVE ANY INCOME THAT YOUR ACCOUNTANT DOES NOT KNOW</b><br/><br/>
	<b>Received Date*:</b> Date you received the payment or the date on the cheque<br/>
	<b>Serviced Date*:</b> Date of the statement or date on which the Sx was performed.<br/>
	<b>Payment Source:</b> Professional for income from medical services else Other for all other income like rental or interest. For payments with no services or other income, uncheck the reconcile checkbox.<br/>
	<b>Payment Type:</b> Select the mode of payment. If it is cash Payment, that you do not to wish to deposit in the bank, the same will be stored in your system as cash in hand<br/> 
	<b>Cheque number:</b> Compulsory for cheque type of payments<br/>
	<b>Amount:</b> Total amount including the TDS<br/>
	<b>In-hand Amount:</b>  Amount on your cheque net of TDS deduction<br/>
	<b>TDS:</b> Modify the % as applicable. The default is 10% for professional income and 0% for other income.<br/>
	<b>Location*:</b> Who gave this payment?<br/>
	<b>Deposited In*:</b> Bank where you deposited the check or cash. If the payment is cash and no bank is selected, the amount will be recorded as cash in hand.<br/>
	
	*Fields that have memory. If you enter data once, it will remember that entry for future records so that you donâ€™t have to enter the entire term next time.
	<br/><br/>
	<b>Buttons</b><br/>
	<b>Save:</b> to save the payment record you  just entered.<br/>
	<b>Save and Main:</b> Go back to go to Home screen after saving.<br/>
	<b>Cancel:</b> Go back to go to Home screen without saving.<br/>
</div>
</body>
</html>